21/02/2006
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- An EU mission arrived in Bulgaria on Monday (20 February) to assess the country's performance under the Justice and Home Affairs chapter. According to the head of the National Border Police Service, General Krassimir Petrov, the monitoring would continue for five days and focus on implementation of the strategy for integrated border management. He stressed Bulgaria's readiness to assume responsibility for its 1,647km of external EU borders, once the country becomes a formal member of the Union. (Sega - 21/02/06; BNR - 20/02/06)
